<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Sm 61/185: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-24T20:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">January 24,
                                        1922—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received January 25, 10:35
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. Letter accrediting me as Chargé d’Affaires erroneously refers to
                            “Republic of Hungary”. Minister for Foreign Affairs has consented to
                            accept it provisionally until the receipt of letter referring to
                            “Kingdom of Hungary”.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>